Privacy Policy – Focus App (Next Horizon Apps by Elif Topuz)

Effective Date: September 27, 2025

1. Introduction

Next Horizon Apps by Elif Topuz (“we,” “our,” or “us”) respects your privacy and is committed to protecting it. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle your personal information when you use the Focus App.

2. Information We Collect

We do not collect any personal information from users through this app. The app does not access your location, contacts, device information, or any other personal data.

3. Third-Party Services

We do not share, sell, or disclose any user information to third parties. We also do not use Google APIs, tracking technologies, or offer walls.

4. Security Measures

Although we do not collect personal data, we implement general security measures to ensure the app is safe and secure.

5. Users’ Rights

Since we do not collect personal information, there are no user profiles or personal data to view, edit, or delete. For privacy-related inquiries, you may contact us at:

Email: nexthorizonapp@gmail.com

Users may use the same email to exercise any rights they may have under applicable privacy laws.

6. Data Protection Officer

We do not currently have a Data Protection Officer (DPO), as the app does not collect personal data and does not target EU/UK users.

7. US State Privacy Laws

This policy is designed to comply with applicable US state privacy laws, including:

CCPA/CPRA (California)

CPA (Colorado)

FDBR (Florida)

TDPSA (Texas)
(and other relevant US state privacy laws as applicable)

8. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected in the Effective Date above.

9. Contact Us

For any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

Email: nexthorizonapp@gmail.com
